A Chinese grandmother tried to sell her eight-year-old grandson in a bid to raise enough money to pay for an operation for her dying son, it has been reported.

Liu Xiaoying, 57, was forced to beg in the street after her family spent all of their money and borrowed thousands more Yuan to pay for medical fees after her 30-year-old son was diagnosed with leukaemia.

The family had used up all of the 100,000 Yuan (£9,515) savings and had borrowed another 200,000 Yuan (£19,000) for the medical fees for her son Dusai.

