They reportedly still needed a further 300,000 Yuan for an operation which could save his life.

The man's mother and his wife however had already sold the family truck, mortgaged their home and borrowed everything they could from friends and other family members.

Liu then started to beg on the street, kneeling beside the road in the city of Wuhan, in China's Hubei province, and asked passersby if they wanted to purchase her eight-year-old grandson.

A police spokesman said: 'The family had little money and now it is all gone

'They are deeply in debt trying to pay for medical treatment to keep her son alive.

The grandmother was questioned and told media when she was released: 'Of course I felt ashamed but I would have sold him to a decent family if I'd had an offer, and with the money I got I would have tried to save my own son.'  

